      },
      "text": "In conclusion, the 2026 FIFA World Cup is much more than a football tournament. It is a global event that combines sports, culture, economics, tourism, and politics. Donald Trump, as President of the United States during the tournament, has played an important role in the preparations and organization of the event. His leadership has generated both support and criticism, reflecting the different political opinions that exist within society. At the same time, the World Cup continues to remind people that football has the power to unite millions across national, cultural, and political differences. While political debates may continue, many people hope that the lasting memory of the 2026 FIFA World Cup will be the excitement of the matches, the celebration of different cultures, and the friendships created through the world's most popular sport.",
